lflings!</span><hr size=1> It's not much, just a story I wrote way back when vind was just a lil sk. Hope you enjoy it.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Stalking silently through the trees, Vindayyan crept slowly following the tracks he had found. He had heard rumors from others but had not believed that even those vermin the Halflings, would have the audacity to come to Nektulos Forest. <br>
<br>
He had set out today to hunt the young Kodiak bears that were often about the forest this time of year, when he had run across a large foot shaped track. He had followed them all evening, now he was drawing close to the Halflings, he could hear their deep voices as they were discussing some nonsense about trees or some other silly thing. <br>
<br>
Ghosting from tree to tree he could catch glimpses of their over large heads an stunted bodies. Smiling to himself as a plan came to him he began moving more rapidly through the forest, he knew the lay of land as well as any who had grown up in Neriak playing in her forests. He found what he sought just as he knew he would, a moss covered dead fall, the corpse of a fallen tree, it was tall enough to conceal himself on one side just near where the filthy Halflings would pass. there had only been two of them with luck he would have one dead before the other would know he was even there.<br>
 <br>
Drawing the axe from the sheath he had rigged to wear upon his back and securing his grip on his shield, he waited almost completely motionless except for the rise an fall of his chest. As the Halflings neared he could see that luck was on his side one of them had fallen slightly behind searching the brush for something as he walked. Vindayyan waited, as the lead Halfling passed his place of hiding he waited till the other stopped again to look through the brush. Then swift as the night wind he struck at the foul Halfling who had passed with in inches of him only moments before, his axe tore ruthlessly through his victims neck sending the over large head whistling through the air followed by a gout of hot blood. The sound of the axe cutting through his companions neck must have alerted the other Halfling to Deaths presence in the wood: As the young Shadow knight turned on his next victim he saw the Halflings hands begin to glow with a fey light. Rushing forward he slammed his shield in to the hated Druids face as he swung with his axe, the Halfling didn't so much dodge the axe-blade but as he moved to the side he lost his footing an tumbled to the soft damp soil of the forests floor leaving the axe to cleave empty air, moving swiftly Vindayyan recovered from his missed blow an brought the axe up in an overhand swing that came crashing down on the Halflings skull nearly splitting it in two. <br>
<br>
&quot;it's Halflings like you that have ruined your own lands!!&quot; he muttered.<br>
<br>
Whistling to himself Vindayyan began looking over the bodies, he came across a few small items of worth but nothing wondrous, he also found grass necklaces on the both the corpses, these he tucked inside his leather jerkin deciding that he would give them to one of the leaders of his guild to prove that the Halflings had indeed invaded Nektulos as rumor had said.  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=428325">Vind Darkheart</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vindayyan>Vindayyan</A> at: 3/25/03 9:37:07 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raiynominouscloud>Raiyn Ominouscloud</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/25/03 6:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=34.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Halflings!</span><hr size=1> /wave Vindayyan!  Remember me from CC?  <br>
